
Explanation of the output

- Each dot (`.`) represents a passed test case.
- In this suite there are four test methods, so you’ll see four dots.
- The line `[100%]` indicates that the test run completed fully.
- `4 passed` confirms that all four tests succeeded.
- `in 0.32s` shows the total execution time (the duration will differ on your machine).

If any test fails, pytest would display an `F` (or more) and a detailed traceback indicating which assertion failed, allowing you to diagnose the issue.
